cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fog computing, which is a networking paradigm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the placement of application components onto infrastructure nodes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm to solve the placement problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper uses an Integer Linear Programming formulation and a Tabu Search-based algorithm. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the modeling of application component execution sequences.
